               <physDesc>
                  <p>(1) Thanks to Emmanuel Francis for providing us with the reference to this
                     colophon and a draft translation of its content. (2) In the date, the nakṣatra
                     is wrong: the colophon records atta (13th nakṣatra), but it should be pūrāṭam
                     or uttirādam (20th and 21st nakṣatras, respectively). One could alternatively
                     read attama-kuru°, “at sunset, on a Thursday”, although it would be unsusual to
                     have an indefinite information as “at sunset” compounded with the name of the
                     day of the week; moreover, the first member of the compound would lack the
                     final °k (attamam + k° > attamak + k°). </p>
               </physDesc>
